sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM professors
WHERE research_interests LIKE '%Aerodynamics%';

external_knowledge:
- "wise keepers" refers to professors;
- "seekers" refers to students;
- "garden of scholarly pursuits" refers to the courses offered within a department;
- "academic blossoms" is a metaphor for GPA, representing the academic performance of students.

sql:
SELECT students.student_name, feedback.comments
FROM students
JOIN feedback ON students.student_id = feedback.student_id;

SELECT departments.department_name, courses.title, courses.credits
FROM departments
JOIN courses ON departments.department_id = courses.department_id;

SELECT department_name, chairperson
FROM departments
WHERE budget > (SELECT AVG(budget) FROM departments);

SELECT professors.name, courses.title
FROM professors
INNER JOIN courses ON professors.professor_id = courses.course_id;

external_knowledge:
Decent feedback refers to ratings of 3 or higher on a scale of 1 to 5;
Average ratings are calculated by averaging all feedback ratings for a course;
Courses are ranked based on their average rating, with higher ratings indicating better reviews.

- "flowers" is a metaphor for courses;
- "gardeners" refers to professors teaching the courses;
- "sweetness" is used metaphorically to describe the GPA of the grades, indicating the academic success or quality of education;
- "fruits" symbolizes the grades received by the students in the courses.

sql:
